WEBVTT

00:12.000 --> 00:14.000
[continuous guttural chanting]

00:19.500 --> 00:22.500
[more voices join in chanting]

00:26.583 --> 00:27.875
[breath exhaling]

00:35.000 --> 00:36.458
[chanting grows louder]

00:41.541 --> 00:43.208
[distant screaming]

01:02.625 --> 01:04.041
[woman] My dearest father...

01:05.750 --> 01:08.541
I pray that you have not been consumed
with worry

01:08.625 --> 01:11.041
in the time that has passed
since I was taken.

01:16.833 --> 01:20.250
I write to you in the hope that you will
put an end to my suffering

01:20.333 --> 01:21.916
on this wretched island.

01:23.250 --> 01:26.458
My captors inform me
that if I am to survive,

01:26.541 --> 01:30.458
you must travel here alone with the means
to purchase my freedom.

01:31.291 --> 01:34.750
That should a man of law be sent
in your stead, it would seal my fate.

01:35.833 --> 01:38.208
Father, I grow weary.

01:39.083 --> 01:41.916
"I fear our Lord no longer hears
my prayer.

01:43.541 --> 01:45.458
Yet still, I pray for your presence...

01:46.708 --> 01:47.750
for my savior.

01:49.250 --> 01:50.416
Please bring me home.

01:51.583 --> 01:52.791
Your beloved daughter...

01:54.125 --> 01:55.166
Jennifer."

02:07.000 --> 02:08.750
The world thinks you're dead.

02:11.458 --> 02:14.875
And then, till I found you,
I thought the same.

02:16.041 --> 02:17.708
That ransom letter...

02:19.708 --> 02:20.916
it was addressed to him.

02:32.625 --> 02:33.458
Look at him.

02:35.541 --> 02:36.750
He's broken.

02:39.541 --> 02:40.416
He lost.

02:42.708 --> 02:46.416
Doesn't even know you're here...
let alone that she's gone.

02:49.083 --> 02:50.916
Whatever ill there is that stands...

02:51.625 --> 02:54.125
stands between you and him,
not your sister.

02:56.041 --> 02:57.416
She needs you, Thomas.

02:58.041 --> 02:59.083
Now more than ever.

03:05.375 --> 03:06.708
And what of the ransom?

03:09.083 --> 03:10.958
[secretary] They won't be expecting you.

03:11.875 --> 03:13.833
Stay hidden among his flock.

03:14.166 --> 03:17.000
But do not pay the ransom they seek...

03:17.750 --> 03:19.000
until you see her.

03:19.916 --> 03:20.833
Alive.

03:21.666 --> 03:22.791
These people...

03:23.375 --> 03:24.833
they're blasphemers...

03:25.333 --> 03:27.166
a cult, a disease.

03:28.166 --> 03:30.791
Be careful. Be smart.

03:32.541 --> 03:33.833
Bring her home.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.125
[panting]

03:48.791 --> 03:50.791
[exhaling]

03:55.125 --> 03:57.875
[train brakes squealing]

04:00.083 --> 04:02.250
[train whistle]

04:04.500 --> 04:06.083
[steam hissing]

04:12.000 --> 04:14.000
[distant clanging]

04:26.791 --> 04:28.375
[man] Have your tickets ready, please.

04:33.875 --> 04:39.375
All printed materials, corrupting images,
ornaments, decorations from the mainland

04:39.458 --> 04:41.291
are strictly forbidden.

04:41.666 --> 04:44.458
Clothing... and heirlooms only.

04:51.458 --> 04:52.708
Welcome, brother.

04:57.958 --> 04:59.000
Welcome, brother.

05:03.458 --> 05:04.875
Welcome, brother.

05:09.125 --> 05:10.333
Welcome, sister.

05:14.333 --> 05:15.416
Welcome, brother.

05:19.750 --> 05:20.791
Welcome, brother.

05:26.166 --> 05:27.166
Welcome, sister.

05:30.708 --> 05:33.125
-May I help you, brother?
-Much thanks, sir.

05:34.541 --> 05:35.458
[man] Welcome, brother.

05:41.375 --> 05:42.375
Welcome, brother.

05:49.291 --> 05:50.291
Welcome, sister.

05:54.250 --> 05:55.083
[man 2] Thank you, sir.

05:55.458 --> 05:56.333
[man] Welcome, brother.

06:03.791 --> 06:04.916
Welcome, brother.

06:13.250 --> 06:14.333
Welcome, sister.

06:22.125 --> 06:23.000
Welcome, brother.

06:32.000 --> 06:34.000
[waves crashing]

06:34.708 --> 06:35.625
[man] Full ahead!

06:49.208 --> 06:51.041
-Brother...
-Sister.

06:51.125 --> 06:52.875
Forgive me, it's just...

06:53.666 --> 06:56.625
I don't recall having seen you
at any prayer meetings.

06:57.416 --> 06:58.333
Nor I you.

06:59.500 --> 07:01.000
Some happenstance?

07:01.583 --> 07:03.541
Quite. Only...

07:04.250 --> 07:05.458
Only we meet now.

07:06.750 --> 07:07.583
We do.

07:09.750 --> 07:11.916
[distressed bleating and grunting]

07:15.291 --> 07:17.291
[bleating and grunting continues]

07:19.750 --> 07:22.083
[frightened bleating intensifies]

07:24.958 --> 07:25.791
[splash]

07:27.083 --> 07:28.958
[bleating fading away]

07:29.958 --> 07:31.291
It was as intended.

07:32.458 --> 07:34.750
Only She decides whether to give or take.

07:36.000 --> 07:37.583
We do not intervene.

07:38.916 --> 07:42.833
[all chanting] Amen.

08:40.583 --> 08:41.541
Let me, sir.

08:56.750 --> 08:59.083
[speaking indistinctly]

10:04.208 --> 10:06.416
[children shouting and playing]

10:29.875 --> 10:31.250
Welcome to Erisden, sir.

10:31.875 --> 10:34.916
-Should you need anything--
-I don't need anything, boy.

10:50.250 --> 10:51.083
Ffion.

10:51.958 --> 10:54.375
-Prepare the table.
-Aye, Father.

10:57.875 --> 11:01.625
[man] All new citizens, please line up.

11:04.416 --> 11:05.250
Oh, my!

11:05.333 --> 11:07.333
[laughing]

11:22.000 --> 11:24.333
Open your mouth, please.
Put your tongue out.

11:26.041 --> 11:27.125
Okay, thank you.

11:32.875 --> 11:34.875
-Name?
-Elaine Williams.

11:35.791 --> 11:37.541
[writing on paper]

11:39.125 --> 11:40.958
-Age?
-Thirty-eight.

11:41.500 --> 11:43.958
-Hello. Let's look here.
-[clerk] Skill or trade?

11:44.041 --> 11:45.791
-[Elaine] Seamstress.
-Okay.

11:45.875 --> 11:49.541
-[clerk] Tell of your donation.
-[Elaine] I offer my undying devotion...

11:49.625 --> 11:52.000
Open your mouth
and put your tongue out, please.

11:52.083 --> 11:54.875
-[Elaine] ...drop of my blood to Our Lady.
-[clerk] As we should.

11:55.833 --> 11:56.791
[clerk] Criminal record?

11:58.208 --> 11:59.125
Vagrancy.

12:01.208 --> 12:04.250
Worry not, Elaine.
You'll want for nothing here.

12:07.666 --> 12:09.166
Please take your receptacle.

12:13.041 --> 12:14.750
Welcome to Erisden, Elaine.

12:14.833 --> 12:15.666
That's good.

12:23.500 --> 12:24.500
Name?

12:26.000 --> 12:27.125
Thomas Richardson.

13:07.875 --> 13:09.541
[bell chiming]

13:33.833 --> 13:40.041
[men and women] ♪ Broad is the road
that leads to death ♪

13:40.625 --> 13:46.000
♪ And thousands walk together there... ♪

13:46.916 --> 13:50.333
[singing continuing faintly]

13:57.166 --> 13:59.708
[hurried footsteps approaching]

14:00.208 --> 14:01.708
How long ago did he begin?

14:01.791 --> 14:03.875
I have no idea.

14:03.958 --> 14:06.083
At least I'm not the last to arrive.
He hates that.

14:06.166 --> 14:08.291
You've got, uh... something on your...

14:22.333 --> 14:23.166
Don't tell.

14:46.041 --> 14:53.000
♪ ...And makes his own destruction sure ♪

14:55.333 --> 14:56.583
[man shouting] Radicalist!

14:57.916 --> 14:59.125
Conspirator.

15:01.583 --> 15:02.666
Traitor!

15:05.083 --> 15:06.666
Enemy of the King.

15:09.041 --> 15:11.916
Those are the words
they attributed to me...

15:13.166 --> 15:16.666
as they shackled my hands
and the hands of my brothers...

15:17.916 --> 15:20.625
before they imprisoned us
on the charge of treason.

15:22.625 --> 15:24.375
Sentenced to death.

15:26.500 --> 15:27.416
But for what?

15:29.958 --> 15:34.875
My only crime was to dare to dream
of a world

15:35.666 --> 15:39.125
in which each waking day we rise equal.

15:39.791 --> 15:42.625
Compassion is no crime.

15:45.083 --> 15:49.291
But my fate was not to be found in death,
my friends.

15:50.541 --> 15:51.375
No, no.

15:52.416 --> 15:55.000
Three brothers we became...

15:56.916 --> 15:58.583
bonded by our escape.

16:00.083 --> 16:04.208
Stowaways, cast into the rough seas.

16:05.875 --> 16:09.916
Oh, the taste of the ocean beating down
my throat, I shall never forget.

16:10.916 --> 16:11.750
But...

16:13.958 --> 16:15.041
nor will I...

16:16.583 --> 16:18.958
the sweet, sweet sound...

16:21.791 --> 16:23.000
of her voice...

16:26.291 --> 16:28.833
as she beckoned us out of the storm.

16:33.375 --> 16:34.416
She...

16:36.125 --> 16:38.166
the goddess of this island,

16:39.541 --> 16:40.916
who saved us...

16:43.333 --> 16:44.500
and who chose my...

16:46.750 --> 16:50.250
chose my tongue... through which to speak.

16:52.666 --> 16:56.833
A man who once walked godless,

16:58.625 --> 17:01.208
she gifted me her wisdom,

17:02.375 --> 17:08.541
entrusted me that I may enrich...
your minds.

17:18.625 --> 17:24.166
I ask you all... where is the land
which has no call for wars?

17:25.333 --> 17:26.166
Hmm?

17:26.625 --> 17:30.041
Arms? Money? Nor taxes?

17:32.541 --> 17:33.916
Well, that land is here.

17:36.250 --> 17:40.958
No tax-gatherer's bill shall ever
threaten our church door!

17:41.375 --> 17:42.791
We, I tell thee, we...

17:44.833 --> 17:45.875
we are free men.

17:54.875 --> 17:56.583
[whispering]

18:06.000 --> 18:07.708
[children laughing]

18:08.583 --> 18:10.375
[girl] Come on! Let's play!

18:10.458 --> 18:11.625
[boy] Wait for me!

18:30.333 --> 18:32.375
[gasping]

18:47.625 --> 18:49.291
[door closes]

18:49.375 --> 18:50.416
What's this?

18:51.166 --> 18:52.708
He wouldn't tell us where the money is.

18:53.458 --> 18:55.875
Well, now you've so broken the man,
he can't tell us...

18:57.208 --> 18:58.416
even if he wanted to!

19:03.500 --> 19:05.583
-You've brought the wrong man.
-It's him.

19:05.666 --> 19:09.250
Of course it's him.
He's the one that gave me this.

19:09.333 --> 19:10.458
It has the mark.

19:15.958 --> 19:17.208
[Malcolm sighing]

19:19.833 --> 19:22.333
[breathing heavily]

19:26.708 --> 19:27.875
My brother.

19:29.875 --> 19:34.958
[sighing] I have promised you a life of
riches without the icy sting of suffering,

19:36.625 --> 19:38.041
greed, and injustice.

19:39.833 --> 19:40.958
And yet here you are...

19:43.458 --> 19:44.625
and there you suffer.

19:48.875 --> 19:49.958
-[groaning]
-Ssh, ssh.

20:18.333 --> 20:20.000
We have an intruder on our land.

20:21.250 --> 20:25.333
He's out there... somewhere.
He knows to remain hidden.

20:27.166 --> 20:28.250
We have to find him.

20:30.958 --> 20:32.958
[lively folk music playing]

20:42.750 --> 20:44.750
[laughter and chatter]

20:56.083 --> 20:57.791
[door slamming]

21:00.083 --> 21:01.291
[door slamming closed]

21:45.666 --> 21:46.666
Did you miss me?

21:48.791 --> 21:51.000
You were only away for two sunsets.

21:51.458 --> 21:53.416
Aye, and two sunrises.

21:53.500 --> 21:55.500
[chuckles]

21:56.083 --> 21:59.708
One day, I promise,
we won't have to hide like this.

22:00.375 --> 22:03.250
We'll have our own house,
with our own name.

22:05.541 --> 22:07.708
We can take this boat and use the wood.

22:09.083 --> 22:10.250
[chuckles] You'll....

22:10.916 --> 22:13.583
You're going to build me a house
using this now, are you?

22:13.666 --> 22:16.000
No, you're right.
It's a stupid... stupid idea.

22:16.083 --> 22:16.916
No.

22:18.375 --> 22:19.208
I'm sorry.

22:21.750 --> 22:22.666
It's beautiful.

22:25.375 --> 22:28.250
And look, we have enough to make
a front door,

22:28.833 --> 22:31.125
enough to carve the name
of our home onto it,

22:31.208 --> 22:33.250
and we can hang it up in the rafters.

22:33.833 --> 22:37.958
And everyone who knows us,
they'll see... and they'll know it's ours.

22:41.250 --> 22:43.708
No one will ever stop me
taking care of you.

22:43.791 --> 22:45.083
I love you, Jeremy.

22:54.708 --> 22:56.416
Ffion, we shouldn't.

22:57.541 --> 22:58.583
It's all right.

23:03.666 --> 23:05.083
I'm with you, Jeremy.

23:14.375 --> 23:16.375
[breathing heavily]

23:21.083 --> 23:23.250
[waves gently crashing]

23:24.666 --> 23:27.208
[wood creaking rhythmically]

23:31.416 --> 23:33.416
Call to quarters!

23:35.208 --> 23:36.625
Back to your dwellings!

23:37.791 --> 23:39.625
The hour of night is here.

23:40.833 --> 23:42.791
Call to quarters!

23:42.875 --> 23:45.083
[drunken laughter and shouting]

23:50.125 --> 23:51.375
[distant door slamming]

24:18.958 --> 24:19.875
Ah.

24:34.500 --> 24:35.416
Sorry.

25:22.500 --> 25:24.958
[footsteps]

26:28.416 --> 26:29.375
Shh.

26:30.333 --> 26:31.166
It's okay.

28:09.916 --> 28:10.791
[gasping]

28:31.875 --> 28:33.833
[key turning]

28:53.250 --> 28:55.541
[gasping and shrieking]

31:04.666 --> 31:06.625
-[knocking at door]
-[coughs]

31:10.708 --> 31:11.791
[further knocking]

31:15.166 --> 31:16.000
Who is it?

31:16.791 --> 31:19.208
[Jeremy] It's, um... It's me, sir.

31:35.708 --> 31:36.583
What is it?

31:38.708 --> 31:39.541
Time for work.

31:47.166 --> 31:48.916
[hammering]

31:55.708 --> 31:57.875
[sawing]

32:06.041 --> 32:07.416
Five more, and she'll do!

32:07.791 --> 32:08.708
Five more!

32:13.416 --> 32:14.250
What is it?

32:14.750 --> 32:18.750
Uh, sir, last night, I'd like to know
why you... What--

32:18.833 --> 32:20.041
Why was I outside?

32:21.541 --> 32:22.875
I was having a cigarette.

32:23.958 --> 32:24.791
Why were you?

32:28.375 --> 32:29.416
Such distrust.

32:30.000 --> 32:32.250
And I was of a mind
I could put my faith in you.

32:32.333 --> 32:34.333
Sorry, sir. I beg your forgiveness.

32:34.416 --> 32:36.750
I mean no insult or quarrel, I just...

32:38.416 --> 32:40.291
I have limited thought, and...

32:41.541 --> 32:42.541
Sorry.

32:50.375 --> 32:52.083
No, I apologize, Jeremy.

32:54.791 --> 32:56.083
Forgive my lack of grace.

32:57.458 --> 32:59.125
I will gladly forgive you, sir...

33:02.583 --> 33:04.333
so long as you'll be so good
as to help me?

33:06.208 --> 33:07.125
With what?

33:12.416 --> 33:13.916
You dragged this here by yourself?

33:14.958 --> 33:16.333
Not I. A man.

33:17.708 --> 33:21.000
Malcolm, he says the man wanted
to bring death here. Says he was a spy.

33:21.583 --> 33:23.291
He tried to leave, but the sea took him.

33:24.833 --> 33:26.125
She protected us.

33:30.666 --> 33:31.500
Did she?

33:40.000 --> 33:41.666
Do many seek to leave the island?

33:42.125 --> 33:43.458
Just the blasphemers.

33:47.166 --> 33:49.083
Are they granted safe passage?

33:49.166 --> 33:51.666
Why do you ask, sir?
You've been here but a day.

33:52.375 --> 33:54.041
I can trust you, can't I, Jeremy?

33:54.500 --> 33:56.500
Of course, sir. What bothers you?

34:01.916 --> 34:03.791
-Sir, I must go now.
-No, you don't!

34:06.708 --> 34:09.125
You know her. Yes, you do,
I can see that you do.

34:10.500 --> 34:12.416
For Christ's sake, be a man, not a child.

34:12.500 --> 34:15.291
-I don't know of what you speak.
-You're lying!

34:15.375 --> 34:16.958
Please, I should go. I should.

34:17.791 --> 34:20.666
Look her in the eye and lie to me again.
You know her.

34:20.750 --> 34:21.708
Say it.

34:27.083 --> 34:27.916
I knew her.

34:30.958 --> 34:32.916
A month ago, she was on our boat.

34:35.250 --> 34:36.666
Frank said we had no choice.

34:38.583 --> 34:41.458
The crops are failing,
the animals have stopped breeding.

34:42.791 --> 34:45.458
We have no means to smuggle food
in from the mainland.

34:47.875 --> 34:49.291
He said her father was rich,

34:49.416 --> 34:51.666
but we only wanted his money
so we wouldn't starve.

34:53.083 --> 34:54.041
But it never came.

34:56.166 --> 34:58.625
[muffled whimpering]

35:04.625 --> 35:06.541
[muffled screaming]

35:24.375 --> 35:25.666
Why didn't you help her?

35:27.083 --> 35:28.416
Look at me, Mr. Richardson.

35:29.166 --> 35:31.666
If they thought I had any part,
if they caught her in my charge--

35:31.750 --> 35:32.916
They? Who's they?

35:33.041 --> 35:35.916
Prophet Malcolm's guards.
Please, sir, I beg of you.

35:36.541 --> 35:38.708
If you are in possession of the ransom
they seek, do not pay it.

35:47.833 --> 35:49.166
You, boy, are in my charge.

35:49.791 --> 35:52.166
If you wish to keep your affair
with that girl in the shadows,

35:52.250 --> 35:54.375
you will serve me during my time
on this land,

35:54.458 --> 35:57.416
and hold fast the purpose
of my being here. Do you understand?

36:00.458 --> 36:01.291
Good.

36:04.458 --> 36:06.583
-[distressed bleating]
-[Malcolm] Hold her down, for fuck's sake!

36:08.708 --> 36:10.208
Jesus, it's turned.

36:11.416 --> 36:12.458
Pull.

36:17.125 --> 36:19.458
[man straining and grunting]

36:25.166 --> 36:27.375
[feeble bleating]

36:35.125 --> 36:36.666
We cannot go on like this.

36:41.666 --> 36:43.458
[panting]

36:43.541 --> 36:45.833
She will gift us another pure harvest.

36:47.250 --> 36:48.166
Have faith.

36:53.041 --> 36:54.833
[bell clanging]

36:57.541 --> 37:01.458
All new arrivals,
please make your way to the church!

37:21.000 --> 37:21.916
Ffion?

37:23.958 --> 37:24.833
What is it?

37:25.875 --> 37:26.750
Tell me.

37:33.958 --> 37:36.750
You're... you're knowledgeable.

37:39.541 --> 37:40.875
You would know if I...

37:41.666 --> 37:42.958
if I should be with child.

37:46.416 --> 37:48.416
Well, first, you and Jeremy
would have to...

37:48.833 --> 37:51.125
Frequently... For many moons.

38:04.458 --> 38:06.208
Andrea, I know what we do is a sin.

38:07.458 --> 38:08.500
Do you love him?

38:09.583 --> 38:10.583
With all my heart.

38:11.291 --> 38:13.375
Then do not judge yourself as sinners.

38:15.958 --> 38:17.416
When was it you last bled?

38:18.666 --> 38:19.791
The winter months.

38:21.166 --> 38:22.833
That may already be your answer.

38:24.083 --> 38:26.041
But there are ways to see...

38:26.458 --> 38:27.541
To know--

38:27.625 --> 38:28.458
Sorry.

38:33.958 --> 38:36.333
All new arrivals are requested
at the church.

38:48.791 --> 38:50.333
As the leader of this community,

38:50.416 --> 38:53.875
it seems I have failed to make clear
the rules...

38:55.041 --> 38:56.250
that bind us.

38:59.166 --> 39:01.083
Under no circumstances...

39:01.583 --> 39:04.583
are any members of this village,
new or old,

39:05.791 --> 39:10.541
permitted to venture out
after the ringing of the night bell.

39:12.083 --> 39:14.666
But last night... [chuckles]

39:15.458 --> 39:16.625
one of you...

39:18.083 --> 39:18.958
broke that rule.

39:23.458 --> 39:26.333
Kneel... if you would be so kind.

39:35.208 --> 39:36.208
Book of Therese,

39:37.041 --> 39:38.875
verse seven, chapter 12.

39:39.625 --> 39:41.166
"For I shall profit not...

39:42.500 --> 39:44.166
I will seek not..."

39:46.958 --> 39:48.625
"...the gold of my brother,

39:49.791 --> 39:52.416
for he hath not more than I,
nor I than him.

39:53.166 --> 39:54.083
For my life--"

39:54.166 --> 39:55.125
Shh, shh.

40:03.625 --> 40:06.000
"For my life is not defined
by consumption,

40:06.083 --> 40:08.208
wealth, and material goods.

40:08.791 --> 40:12.208
It is an echo of my neighbor
and of my neighbor's neighbor.

40:13.708 --> 40:14.833
We, the people of--"

40:15.958 --> 40:17.916
[Malcolm's footsteps approaching]

40:19.083 --> 40:21.208
[man] "We, the people of Erisden,

40:21.833 --> 40:23.541
stand bonded in our unity,

40:24.125 --> 40:26.250
stand united through equality,

40:26.333 --> 40:27.625
for we shall suffer not,

40:28.541 --> 40:29.541
shall want not."

40:46.791 --> 40:47.666
Well?

40:52.791 --> 40:54.583
For King and country!

40:56.541 --> 40:57.791
[both grunting]

41:00.583 --> 41:01.625
Agh!

41:04.041 --> 41:06.791
[panting]

41:42.166 --> 41:44.166
This heathen land...

41:45.708 --> 41:48.166
will... burn!

41:52.541 --> 41:53.875
[knife clanging on floor]

41:55.958 --> 41:57.250
[Thomas panting]

41:57.375 --> 41:58.541
[groaning]

42:01.208 --> 42:02.208
Agh!

42:02.833 --> 42:04.208
Treat the man! Do it!

42:05.458 --> 42:06.583
Agh!

42:09.333 --> 42:12.833
He was from the mainland. An assassin.
His knife has the King's markings.

42:13.416 --> 42:15.333
Did you bring anyone at all
that you weren't supposed to?

42:15.500 --> 42:16.708
[Thomas moaning]

42:23.458 --> 42:26.750
If the knife of that bastard
cut just one of us,

42:27.375 --> 42:28.916
we all bleed together.

42:29.583 --> 42:33.333
If your blood has been shed in my name,
I shed mine for you.

42:34.208 --> 42:35.791
-Father!
-[grunts]

42:38.458 --> 42:40.000
I'm indebted to you, brother.

42:40.583 --> 42:42.750
Your act of bravery
shall not go unrewarded.

42:43.291 --> 42:44.333
You have my word.

42:47.416 --> 42:50.333
Today the King sends spies.
How long before he sends ships?

42:51.000 --> 42:53.333
I want spotters stationed
along the coastline.

42:53.416 --> 42:54.500
Strengthen our defense.

42:54.583 --> 42:57.250
-Load the carriages, arm the barricade.
-Aye!

42:57.333 --> 42:59.708
-Travel to the north point.
-To the north point!

43:00.708 --> 43:01.708
[groaning]

43:03.041 --> 43:05.333
[muffled screaming]

43:06.000 --> 43:07.291
We're not done here yet.

43:07.875 --> 43:10.541
The intruder still walks,
and we have a ransom to find.

43:11.458 --> 43:12.875
All right, collect the girl.

43:13.291 --> 43:16.625
If he insists on remaining hidden,
we'll show him the consequences.

43:24.000 --> 43:27.625
[horse trotting and neighing]

43:41.500 --> 43:42.833
Afraid I spilt a little.

43:43.500 --> 43:44.458
How dare you!

43:47.375 --> 43:49.208
How long did this collection take?

43:50.875 --> 43:53.083
Trinkets like these
are not easily acquired.

43:53.750 --> 43:54.833
My uncle.

43:55.500 --> 43:56.750
My mother's kin.

43:57.708 --> 43:58.541
He's a doctor.

44:01.458 --> 44:02.458
Is that your mother?

44:03.750 --> 44:04.583
Yes.

44:05.541 --> 44:06.791
She died giving birth to me.

44:07.708 --> 44:08.833
I'm sorry.

44:11.666 --> 44:13.500
My uncle says I remind him of her.

44:14.583 --> 44:16.875
Says it gives him peace to know
she lives through me.

44:18.583 --> 44:20.916
All my life, he's been the only one
who could look at me,

44:21.000 --> 44:22.583
see her, and still smile.

44:26.083 --> 44:27.041
My father...

44:29.375 --> 44:31.333
sometimes I can just see it his eyes.

44:33.166 --> 44:34.250
A resentment.

44:35.583 --> 44:36.708
Do you resent him?

44:38.166 --> 44:40.500
-Sir?
-Your father, for bringing you here.

44:41.291 --> 44:43.041
-Mr. Richardson--
-Don't misunderstand me.

44:43.125 --> 44:44.583
I'm glad that he did, but...

44:45.666 --> 44:48.083
You strike me as somebody
with more to give this world

44:48.166 --> 44:50.458
than merely being the daughter
of a prophet.

44:54.166 --> 44:56.916
-Do you resent yours?
-Oh, every day.

45:01.875 --> 45:04.166
A few drops of these
should see you through the night.

45:23.125 --> 45:25.125
I'll come by tomorrow
to change your bandages.

45:29.791 --> 45:31.500
Thank you, Miss Howe.

46:13.166 --> 46:15.000
[bell clanging]

46:16.250 --> 46:18.250
[man] Call to quarters!

46:27.125 --> 46:29.125
[Malcolm] People of Erisden!

46:31.041 --> 46:32.291
Hear me!

46:34.416 --> 46:36.250
The woman you see before you...

46:38.041 --> 46:40.458
has broken the laws of our land!

46:43.166 --> 46:46.625
She is an agent of a dying god...

46:47.458 --> 46:49.125
and a weak King.

46:51.083 --> 46:53.208
She's come here to corrupt...

46:54.000 --> 46:55.916
and destroy our community!

46:59.375 --> 47:00.375
But...

47:01.458 --> 47:02.666
there is another.

47:04.833 --> 47:07.208
Her kin is here also.

47:08.583 --> 47:10.250
Co-conspirator!

47:13.333 --> 47:14.958
I call to him now!

47:16.166 --> 47:17.541
Make yourself known.

47:18.791 --> 47:21.416
Make good... on the debt...

47:22.041 --> 47:22.958
that she owes...

47:25.166 --> 47:27.291
and forgiveness shall be hers.

47:29.666 --> 47:31.250
Stay in the shadows...

47:32.708 --> 47:36.000
and it be the Heathen's Stand
that awaits ye both!

47:51.666 --> 47:52.625
Very well.

48:05.750 --> 48:07.541
[Jennifer whimpering]

48:16.916 --> 48:18.916
No! No!

48:19.500 --> 48:21.500
Don't! No!

48:22.958 --> 48:24.083
[crying] No!

48:25.083 --> 48:25.916
No, no!

48:26.000 --> 48:27.375
[screaming]

48:27.458 --> 48:28.291
Stop!

48:29.125 --> 48:29.958
Stop!

48:31.541 --> 48:32.833
Please, no!

48:32.916 --> 48:34.375
[screaming]

48:36.541 --> 48:39.000
[Malcolm] The sands of time are sinking!

48:41.791 --> 48:43.791
Her life is in your hands!

49:39.208 --> 49:41.041
[birds chirping]

50:47.000 --> 50:47.875
[creak]

51:16.208 --> 51:18.375
[laughing]

51:27.750 --> 51:29.875
[boys and girls laughing]

51:48.458 --> 51:49.791
[yells]

51:52.791 --> 51:54.875
Let them play.

52:09.291 --> 52:11.291
[boys resume laughing]

52:38.916 --> 52:40.416
-You good?
-Aye.

52:49.500 --> 52:51.583
We don't have the resources
for this, Malcolm.

52:52.583 --> 52:55.333
These festivities will decimate
our livestock.

52:56.583 --> 52:58.541
Celebrating our way into starvation.

53:01.000 --> 53:03.166
Tonight, while they celebrate...

53:04.083 --> 53:05.625
we'll search their rooms.

53:07.916 --> 53:09.333
If he's here, we'll know it.

53:09.916 --> 53:12.541
First, we find the money, then we'll...

53:14.541 --> 53:17.791
Well, we'll deal with them both.
Trust me, this ends tonight.

53:20.625 --> 53:21.500
Andrea?

53:33.666 --> 53:35.125
Off from her, now!

53:36.500 --> 53:38.416
Can we at least
afford this woman her dignity?

53:53.458 --> 53:55.125
[Jennifer whimpering]

53:55.208 --> 53:56.083
Slowly.

53:57.125 --> 53:58.958
Slowly, or your body will reject it.

54:02.458 --> 54:03.500
Thank you.

54:11.166 --> 54:13.791
I'll see to it that no one harms you.
I promise.

54:15.666 --> 54:16.750
Just hold strong.

54:37.416 --> 54:39.708
[hammering]

54:47.625 --> 54:48.500
[guard] Come on!

54:52.333 --> 54:53.166
Get up!

55:00.958 --> 55:01.791
Go!

55:17.375 --> 55:18.208
Be ready.

55:24.625 --> 55:25.916
[laughing]

55:26.000 --> 55:28.625
-[fiddle and drum music playing]
-[villagers clapping along]

55:56.625 --> 55:58.000
[door opening]

56:22.291 --> 56:23.541
-[imitates gun firing]
-Agh.

56:25.375 --> 56:26.333
[laughing]

56:27.666 --> 56:29.291
[footsteps running away]

56:38.375 --> 56:40.375
[fiddle and drum music]

56:47.708 --> 56:48.708
Good evening.

56:51.250 --> 56:53.250
[laughter and chatter]

56:56.750 --> 56:57.833
Well, hello.

56:59.083 --> 57:00.125
What's all this?

57:00.291 --> 57:02.750
There's more to life
than harvest and prayer, Mr. Richardson.

57:02.833 --> 57:05.291
It's called "fun". You should try it.

57:05.416 --> 57:08.250
-Thomas.
-Are you going to ask me to dance?

57:08.333 --> 57:11.500
[chuckles] It would be an honor,
my lady, but...

57:12.166 --> 57:14.250
do you think the prophet will permit?

57:15.000 --> 57:16.750
I'm not sure my father would be persuaded.

57:18.458 --> 57:22.375
I sincerely doubt he'd be happy
with hands such as these...

57:23.083 --> 57:24.750
on the hips of his good little girl.

57:30.750 --> 57:33.000
These are far from scholarly hands,
Mr. Richardson.

57:33.750 --> 57:34.708
Thomas.

57:35.958 --> 57:37.666
And I never proclaimed to be as such.

57:39.791 --> 57:40.666
Your eyes...

57:42.166 --> 57:43.416
they've seen things.

57:48.083 --> 57:49.166
Who are you?

57:51.750 --> 57:53.041
Will you excuse me, Andrea?

57:54.291 --> 57:55.166
Wait.

58:02.000 --> 58:02.916
Come on.

58:11.458 --> 58:13.208
[fiddle and drum music ends]

58:13.291 --> 58:14.875
[applause]

58:16.916 --> 58:19.875
-I found these.
-You've done well. Let's go.

58:24.958 --> 58:27.416
[fiddle and drum music resumes]

58:41.333 --> 58:42.208
[clang]

58:43.000 --> 58:43.833
[clink]

58:52.166 --> 58:53.166
-Are you going--
-[clink]

58:59.333 --> 59:01.125
[hammering in time to the drum]

59:10.708 --> 59:12.375
We're wasting our time here, Quinn.

59:14.583 --> 59:15.916
Every room, Malcolm.

59:18.291 --> 59:19.291
Let's move on!

59:55.958 --> 59:56.875
What is it?

59:59.958 --> 1:00:00.875
It's the house.

1:00:06.458 --> 1:00:08.041
Frank! Frank!

1:00:08.541 --> 1:00:09.375
The house!

1:00:20.208 --> 1:00:22.208
-Close it after. Don't seal it.
-Yes, sir.

1:00:23.958 --> 1:00:26.958
Jeremy... if you meet any trouble...

1:00:27.625 --> 1:00:28.708
use this.

1:00:29.375 --> 1:00:30.458
No matter who it is.

1:00:34.958 --> 1:00:35.833
Thank you.

1:01:05.000 --> 1:01:06.916
[footsteps]

1:01:22.083 --> 1:01:22.916
Agh!

1:01:28.875 --> 1:01:29.750
Get!

1:01:30.625 --> 1:01:31.833
[whimpering]

1:01:33.291 --> 1:01:34.333
Go on, go!

1:01:34.416 --> 1:01:36.125
[footsteps running away]

1:01:45.125 --> 1:01:45.958
[Quinn] Frank!

1:01:47.416 --> 1:01:48.375
Frank!

1:01:48.458 --> 1:01:49.291
Down here.

1:01:53.708 --> 1:01:54.750
He's inside.

1:01:57.625 --> 1:02:00.041
Okay, Frank, take my hunting rifle,
get down there and flush him out.

1:02:00.125 --> 1:02:01.708
Quinn, stand guard should he return.

1:02:04.166 --> 1:02:05.375
Should be me down there.

1:02:05.458 --> 1:02:08.333
I want him a prisoner in possession
of answers, not a corpse.

1:02:31.958 --> 1:02:32.791
Frank.

1:02:53.375 --> 1:02:54.250
Don't hesitate.

1:02:55.541 --> 1:02:56.791
You see him, you shoot him.

1:03:59.000 --> 1:04:00.666
[dripping]

1:04:50.208 --> 1:04:51.458
[horse whinnying]

1:05:09.000 --> 1:05:10.416
[footsteps]

1:06:27.916 --> 1:06:29.500
Wait, don't shoot! It's me!

1:06:30.500 --> 1:06:32.333
Jesus Christ, man!

1:06:37.291 --> 1:06:39.958
[labored breathing]

1:06:43.250 --> 1:06:44.500
[retching]

1:07:05.875 --> 1:07:07.708
-[squealing]
-Agh!

1:07:16.250 --> 1:07:17.083
Ah!

1:07:18.041 --> 1:07:19.583
[gasping for breath]

1:07:42.666 --> 1:07:44.708
[shrieking]

1:07:54.791 --> 1:07:57.333
[gasping and panting]

1:08:02.375 --> 1:08:04.541
[loud wailing]

1:08:09.416 --> 1:08:11.541
[eerie shouting and screaming]

1:08:13.000 --> 1:08:15.666
[hysterical shrieking]

1:08:16.958 --> 1:08:17.916
[sudden silence]

1:08:24.083 --> 1:08:26.208
[dripping]

1:08:39.291 --> 1:08:40.125
What...

1:08:40.208 --> 1:08:42.208
[gasping and panting]

1:08:52.625 --> 1:08:54.833
[gasping]

1:08:58.416 --> 1:09:00.166
[panting]

1:10:15.791 --> 1:10:17.000
You showed yourself.

1:10:19.291 --> 1:10:20.125
To him.

1:10:22.083 --> 1:10:22.916
Why?

1:10:29.458 --> 1:10:30.875
He's not to be trusted.

1:10:34.666 --> 1:10:36.125
He won't worship you...

1:10:37.458 --> 1:10:38.416
as I.

1:10:39.958 --> 1:10:40.791
[groaning]

1:10:41.500 --> 1:10:42.333
Ah.

1:10:50.750 --> 1:10:52.875
[moaning]

1:10:52.958 --> 1:10:55.708
No more shall you poison our crop.

1:10:57.375 --> 1:10:59.208
I swear you shall starve,

1:10:59.291 --> 1:11:01.583
lest you give us pure harvest!

1:11:02.083 --> 1:11:03.416
[gasping]

1:11:05.958 --> 1:11:08.125
[moaning]

1:11:19.916 --> 1:11:21.958
[woman whimpering]

1:11:45.958 --> 1:11:47.666
[muffled protests]

1:11:55.250 --> 1:11:56.583
[panicked crying]

1:11:56.666 --> 1:11:57.833
[woman] No! No!

1:11:57.916 --> 1:11:58.750
No!

1:11:59.458 --> 1:12:00.416
No!

1:12:01.000 --> 1:12:02.333
No!

1:12:03.041 --> 1:12:04.000
No!

1:12:04.416 --> 1:12:05.333
No!

1:12:06.416 --> 1:12:09.208
[grunting and screaming]

1:12:17.208 --> 1:12:18.291
[moaning]

1:12:22.375 --> 1:12:23.333
You found it.

1:12:29.375 --> 1:12:30.333
What is this?

1:12:33.041 --> 1:12:34.125
You wouldn't believe me.

1:12:38.500 --> 1:12:39.333
Here.

1:12:39.916 --> 1:12:41.125
Change into these.

1:13:04.041 --> 1:13:05.083
What happened to you?

1:13:10.416 --> 1:13:11.458
My faith.

1:13:13.416 --> 1:13:15.625
I once held fast a belief in the divine.

1:13:17.250 --> 1:13:18.250
Like you, I...

1:13:19.000 --> 1:13:20.791
knelt before a deity.

1:13:25.958 --> 1:13:28.750
Armed with the book of Jesus Christ, I...

1:13:29.916 --> 1:13:32.750
led my parish into the heart of Peking.

1:13:35.083 --> 1:13:39.541
And we showed them the glory
and the love of God himself...

1:13:41.833 --> 1:13:43.750
and then they showed us the Devil.

1:13:47.125 --> 1:13:48.458
[groaning]

1:13:51.875 --> 1:13:53.125
[loud explosion]

1:13:54.541 --> 1:13:56.333
[horse galloping]

1:13:56.416 --> 1:13:57.625
[man] No!

1:14:08.291 --> 1:14:09.416
[explosion]

1:14:09.833 --> 1:14:11.250
[man screaming]

1:14:18.375 --> 1:14:19.708
-[gunshot]
-[screaming]

1:14:19.791 --> 1:14:21.083
[shouting in Mandarin]

1:14:22.375 --> 1:14:23.541
Agh!

1:14:25.041 --> 1:14:26.875
[gasping and panting]

1:14:26.958 --> 1:14:29.791
Blessed be, my Father,
I beg of You, hear my prayer!

1:14:31.375 --> 1:14:32.333
Agh!

1:14:37.500 --> 1:14:40.333
As Your faithful servant,
in this hour of need,

1:14:40.416 --> 1:14:42.958
I pray for Your divine intervention!

1:14:43.958 --> 1:14:44.875
Agh!

1:14:44.958 --> 1:14:46.208
[woman screaming]

1:14:46.291 --> 1:14:47.833
[shouting in Mandarin]

1:14:49.500 --> 1:14:51.500
[woman screaming]

1:14:56.916 --> 1:14:59.333
Please! Show Yourself!

1:15:00.541 --> 1:15:02.083
[man screaming]

1:15:03.625 --> 1:15:05.333
[cloth ripping]

1:15:09.916 --> 1:15:11.166
Agh!

1:15:19.333 --> 1:15:23.041
The promise of the Divine
is but an illusion.

1:15:24.125 --> 1:15:25.875
Nothing in this world is pure...

1:15:27.041 --> 1:15:28.291
except for Jennifer...

1:15:28.875 --> 1:15:29.875
my sister.

1:15:31.250 --> 1:15:32.250
Always in my heart.

1:15:33.875 --> 1:15:35.833
She did not abandon me then...

1:15:36.791 --> 1:15:38.791
and I will not abandon her now.

1:15:39.916 --> 1:15:41.125
As for God,

1:15:41.666 --> 1:15:45.083
he left me, left all of us to suffer.

1:15:47.583 --> 1:15:48.875
But you survived.

1:15:49.416 --> 1:15:51.166
Only my body, and barely that.

1:15:52.583 --> 1:15:53.833
God is pain...

1:15:53.916 --> 1:15:55.791
is... suffering...

1:15:56.916 --> 1:15:58.208
-is betrayal.
-Is forgiveness.

1:15:58.291 --> 1:15:59.208
Tsk.

1:15:59.833 --> 1:16:01.208
Thomas, let me help you.

1:16:01.791 --> 1:16:03.958
Says the daughter of the man
who wants me dead.

1:16:04.541 --> 1:16:06.750
No. Not I, and not my father.

1:16:06.833 --> 1:16:08.958
Child, you must be blind
to think otherwise.

1:16:09.958 --> 1:16:13.000
He may be many things, Mr. Richardson,
but he's not a murderer.

1:16:14.291 --> 1:16:16.125
-He wouldn't.
-Oh, he would.

1:16:17.375 --> 1:16:18.458
And he has.

1:16:20.583 --> 1:16:25.250
"Beware of false prophets
which come to you in sheep's clothing,

1:16:25.333 --> 1:16:28.500
but inwardly they are ravening wolves."

1:16:28.916 --> 1:16:31.166
Andrea, you know it to be true.

1:16:33.375 --> 1:16:34.666
My sister...

1:16:35.875 --> 1:16:37.250
is no traitor.

1:16:38.250 --> 1:16:39.708
No spy.

1:16:41.083 --> 1:16:42.625
She didn't come here.

1:16:44.333 --> 1:16:45.333
She was taken.

1:16:47.416 --> 1:16:50.208
[waves crashing]

1:17:32.041 --> 1:17:33.041
Frank?

1:17:59.458 --> 1:18:00.625
She provided for us...

1:18:01.666 --> 1:18:02.583
once.

1:18:03.125 --> 1:18:04.708
Enough of your superstition.

1:18:08.291 --> 1:18:09.125
Where are we?

1:18:09.250 --> 1:18:11.666
Worry not.
They won't know to look for you here.

1:18:28.166 --> 1:18:29.208
It's toxic.

1:18:31.958 --> 1:18:34.708
All the crops have become riddled
with impurities.

1:18:38.083 --> 1:18:38.958
Look.

1:18:43.833 --> 1:18:44.791
All this land...

1:18:45.416 --> 1:18:47.791
it's scorched earth that we live upon.

1:18:48.458 --> 1:18:50.416
And yet, somehow, it grows.

1:18:51.458 --> 1:18:52.458
Why now?

1:18:53.375 --> 1:18:54.666
I don't know.

1:18:56.125 --> 1:18:57.875
Perhaps her strength is fading.

1:19:00.500 --> 1:19:02.083
Or something has angered her.

1:19:12.458 --> 1:19:13.291
Pregnant?

1:19:32.750 --> 1:19:37.166
Ffion, Frank wants I should travel
with him today to the mainland.

1:19:37.250 --> 1:19:39.583
Then I'll be at shore
to greet you at sunrise.

1:19:40.250 --> 1:19:41.458
He wants I should stay there.

1:19:44.250 --> 1:19:45.083
Jeremy...

1:19:45.166 --> 1:19:48.000
And I want only should you be there
by my side...

1:19:50.458 --> 1:19:51.541
as my wife.

1:19:55.208 --> 1:19:56.458
[chuckles]

1:19:57.958 --> 1:19:59.416
Well, you know yourself,

1:19:59.791 --> 1:20:03.041
your father would never allow it.
Me, you...

1:20:04.708 --> 1:20:05.625
us...

1:20:06.833 --> 1:20:07.791
our child.

1:20:10.958 --> 1:20:12.166
We could be together...

1:20:12.875 --> 1:20:14.541
any time of any day.

1:20:17.125 --> 1:20:19.000
-Free.
-To love each other.

1:20:27.125 --> 1:20:27.958
Wait.

1:20:29.166 --> 1:20:31.375
Wait right here.
I have something... for us.

1:20:44.625 --> 1:20:45.666
[Ffion gasping]

1:21:17.875 --> 1:21:18.708
Father?

1:21:19.166 --> 1:21:20.708
Father, please. I can explain.

1:21:20.791 --> 1:21:22.875
Please! I was going to tell you. Please--

1:21:23.666 --> 1:21:24.583
Agh!

1:21:25.083 --> 1:21:26.458
[sobbing]

1:21:26.583 --> 1:21:27.666
Tell me now!

1:21:28.250 --> 1:21:30.041
What suspicions have ye confirmed?

1:21:30.125 --> 1:21:31.458
Father, no!

1:21:31.541 --> 1:21:32.416
No!

1:21:32.500 --> 1:21:35.833
Inform me, child!
Lest I see what ye hide!

1:21:37.291 --> 1:21:38.708
It's mine to keep!

1:21:56.458 --> 1:21:57.500
Where you going, Frank?

1:22:01.166 --> 1:22:02.416
The boy and me are leaving.

1:22:04.208 --> 1:22:05.166
Frank...

1:22:05.500 --> 1:22:06.416
Sorry, Malcolm.

1:22:07.791 --> 1:22:10.041
I can't be part of this anymore.
I won't.

1:22:11.500 --> 1:22:12.750
This community needs you.

1:22:15.541 --> 1:22:16.375
I need you.

1:22:17.791 --> 1:22:18.875
You need my boat.

1:22:20.625 --> 1:22:22.333
I was happy following you

1:22:22.416 --> 1:22:24.333
when this was all about the word
of your heart.

1:22:24.416 --> 1:22:25.916
Come on, Frank. This...

1:22:26.541 --> 1:22:27.750
this is our island.

1:22:29.250 --> 1:22:30.250
We built this...

1:22:31.041 --> 1:22:34.083
with our own hands. You, me... Quinn.

1:22:35.958 --> 1:22:37.333
It's our paradise.

1:22:37.916 --> 1:22:41.666
No. It's our hell,
and I'm dragging the boy down with me.

1:22:41.750 --> 1:22:43.083
And you, your Andrea.

1:22:44.458 --> 1:22:45.416
No, no.

1:22:45.500 --> 1:22:47.333
No, no, you're wrong, Frank.

1:22:47.916 --> 1:22:50.750
We have homes here. We have families.

1:22:51.916 --> 1:22:53.916
-We have faith.
-[sighing] Oh, faith...

1:22:55.083 --> 1:22:59.250
We have a god in chains
poisoning us from the inside out.

1:22:59.875 --> 1:23:02.333
We have an innocent man's blood
on our hands.

1:23:03.083 --> 1:23:05.500
We have a kidnapped girl, held for ransom.

1:23:05.583 --> 1:23:09.708
I'll go to my grave washing the blood
of that wee soul from my hands.

1:23:10.666 --> 1:23:13.250
This place, this community, it's broken.

1:23:13.333 --> 1:23:14.416
Then we'll fix it!

1:23:22.833 --> 1:23:23.875
Together.

1:23:26.375 --> 1:23:27.583
It's finished.

1:23:28.458 --> 1:23:30.041
You know it in your heart.

1:23:37.958 --> 1:23:38.916
Whose is it?

1:23:42.875 --> 1:23:44.333
Who put that inside you?

1:23:44.875 --> 1:23:45.708
Please...

1:23:46.583 --> 1:23:48.958
Father, do not see it
for the judgment of his actions.

1:23:49.041 --> 1:23:50.875
Oh, no. No, no, no.

1:23:51.458 --> 1:23:52.375
Pray no.

1:23:53.583 --> 1:23:56.333
-Not him.
-He followed only what I asked.

1:23:59.708 --> 1:24:01.875
This is a harlot's tongue!

1:24:02.916 --> 1:24:05.500
Them be a whore's lips
that move before me!

1:24:05.625 --> 1:24:07.250
Look into my eyes,

1:24:07.583 --> 1:24:11.958
and see the daughter that stands
frightened and in need of a father's love!

1:24:12.083 --> 1:24:16.333
You have no idea
what monstrosity grows inside you!

1:24:18.833 --> 1:24:20.541
This is an abomination!

1:24:21.458 --> 1:24:24.375
-A bastard mongoloid breed!
-No!

1:24:24.750 --> 1:24:28.208
To be born in lumps of twisted flesh
no mother would ever call her own.

1:24:28.333 --> 1:24:30.833
-No!
-Yes... child.

1:24:32.458 --> 1:24:33.833
I've seen it.

1:24:36.166 --> 1:24:37.041
I've seen it.

1:24:38.666 --> 1:24:39.791
That thing...

1:24:41.208 --> 1:24:42.500
It will kill you.

1:24:45.041 --> 1:24:46.833
[sobbing]

1:24:51.000 --> 1:24:52.416
I won't stand for it.

1:24:57.666 --> 1:24:58.583
Here.

1:25:00.041 --> 1:25:01.000
No! No!

1:25:01.083 --> 1:25:02.458
No! Stop!

1:25:21.458 --> 1:25:22.500
Ffion?

1:25:30.291 --> 1:25:31.250
[Quinn] You did this.

1:25:38.083 --> 1:25:39.208
You put your seed...

1:25:40.625 --> 1:25:42.833
inside my beautiful angel.

1:25:52.458 --> 1:25:54.166
I had no choice.

1:25:58.833 --> 1:25:59.916
My Ffion.

1:26:01.375 --> 1:26:02.875
My daughter!

1:26:04.750 --> 1:26:05.625
And you...

1:26:07.666 --> 1:26:09.125
took her from me.

1:26:18.833 --> 1:26:19.750
[Quinn] Agh!

1:26:31.208 --> 1:26:32.750
-[razor slicing]
[Quinn] Agh!

1:26:37.666 --> 1:26:38.583
Agh!

1:26:47.250 --> 1:26:49.208
Agh! Agh!

1:26:51.250 --> 1:26:53.000
[screaming]

1:27:02.666 --> 1:27:03.625
Help!

1:27:04.041 --> 1:27:05.833
Help! Help!

1:27:06.833 --> 1:27:08.625
Help! Help!

1:27:09.541 --> 1:27:10.541
Somebody help!

1:27:11.166 --> 1:27:12.375
He killed her!

1:27:13.291 --> 1:27:14.833
He killed my girl!

1:27:15.625 --> 1:27:16.458
No...

1:27:16.833 --> 1:27:17.750
No, I didn't.

1:27:18.625 --> 1:27:19.541
Murderer!

1:27:20.250 --> 1:27:21.833
Don't let him escape!

1:27:22.416 --> 1:27:23.458
After him!

1:27:24.625 --> 1:27:25.625
After him!

1:27:26.333 --> 1:27:27.250
[guard] This way!

1:27:42.541 --> 1:27:44.541
Prepare the Heathen's Stand!

1:27:46.166 --> 1:27:48.916
By order of purification!

1:27:49.000 --> 1:27:51.125
[man] But, sir, only Prophet Malcolm--

1:27:51.250 --> 1:27:54.666
Malcolm is not the divine ruler
of this land!

1:27:59.458 --> 1:28:00.916
Now, follow my orders.

1:28:02.375 --> 1:28:03.458
Or I swear...

1:28:04.375 --> 1:28:06.041
by the blood of my kin...

1:28:06.875 --> 1:28:08.833
ye shall face the same fate.

1:28:11.750 --> 1:28:12.750
Now!

1:28:16.416 --> 1:28:17.875
Sound the alarm.

1:28:20.958 --> 1:28:21.958
[bell clanging]

1:28:41.750 --> 1:28:43.333
[distant bell clanging]

1:28:44.375 --> 1:28:45.375
What's happening?

1:28:54.541 --> 1:28:56.416
[rustling]

1:28:56.500 --> 1:28:58.458
[panting]

1:29:08.541 --> 1:29:09.708
Andrea!

1:29:10.875 --> 1:29:12.208
Jeremy! Jeremy!

1:29:12.291 --> 1:29:15.333
Please, help me. I didn't hurt her.
I swear I didn't touch her!

1:29:15.416 --> 1:29:17.541
What are you talking about?
What's happened?

1:29:18.916 --> 1:29:20.375
Jeremy, where is Ffion?

1:29:21.583 --> 1:29:24.791
I didn't do it! It was him.
He ripped our child from her!

1:29:25.583 --> 1:29:26.625
[striking blows]

1:29:26.708 --> 1:29:28.500
-Jeremy!
-Get back!

1:29:29.291 --> 1:29:32.041
The boy killed her.
He needs to be purified.

1:29:32.125 --> 1:29:33.375
-No!
-Pick him up!

1:29:33.458 --> 1:29:34.375
No!

1:29:34.458 --> 1:29:35.458
Jeremy!

1:29:36.458 --> 1:29:37.625
Jeremy!

1:29:39.416 --> 1:29:40.833
Listen to his words!

1:29:41.041 --> 1:29:42.166
Listen!

1:29:44.333 --> 1:29:45.750
Jeremy! Agh!

1:29:46.208 --> 1:29:47.041
Please!

1:29:47.125 --> 1:29:47.958
Please!

1:29:50.125 --> 1:29:52.125
No! Stop, please!

1:30:17.958 --> 1:30:20.125
[Jeremy screaming]

1:30:42.333 --> 1:30:43.208
[guard] Lift!

1:30:52.458 --> 1:30:53.625
You monster!

1:30:55.875 --> 1:30:57.125
Restrain him!

1:30:59.041 --> 1:31:00.750
You know that boy would never hurt Ffion.

1:31:00.833 --> 1:31:03.125
He has nothing but love
in his heart for her.

1:31:06.000 --> 1:31:08.000
Is this the love of which you speak?

1:31:08.833 --> 1:31:10.583
[Jeremy screaming]

1:31:22.666 --> 1:31:23.875
I, a father...

1:31:26.208 --> 1:31:27.208
robbed of kin,

1:31:29.583 --> 1:31:30.708
even in this,

1:31:31.916 --> 1:31:34.708
-[crunching bone]
-[muffled] a moment of unforgiving grief,

1:31:37.208 --> 1:31:38.458
am merciful.

1:31:38.541 --> 1:31:40.000
[Jeremy whimpering]

1:31:40.958 --> 1:31:41.916
Am I not?

1:31:44.250 --> 1:31:47.916
-How could you? How could you?
-He shall be cleansed...

1:31:48.000 --> 1:31:48.916
[Andrea] Please!

1:31:49.000 --> 1:31:51.541
...according to the edict of this land.

1:31:51.625 --> 1:31:54.375
[Andrea] Don't let this happen!
Please, don't let this happen!

1:31:54.458 --> 1:31:56.791
-[Jeremy gasping]
-[Andrea] Oh, please! Please!

1:31:56.875 --> 1:31:58.000
Let us begin.

1:32:48.958 --> 1:32:50.666
[Jeremy gasping]

1:33:06.916 --> 1:33:08.333
I've wanted this.

1:33:29.416 --> 1:33:30.416
-[crunch]
-[screaming]

1:33:35.416 --> 1:33:37.166
-[crunching bone]
-[Jeremy screaming]

1:33:38.041 --> 1:33:39.583
[Jeremy breathlessly groaning]

1:33:45.208 --> 1:33:46.166
Agh...

1:34:46.083 --> 1:34:47.375
I grant unto thee...

1:34:48.666 --> 1:34:50.333
this symbol of purity.

1:34:53.583 --> 1:34:54.416
Let it guide you.

1:34:58.625 --> 1:35:00.875
[Andrea sobbing]

1:35:06.583 --> 1:35:07.541
Pray for him.

1:35:11.000 --> 1:35:13.166
-[footsteps approaching]
-[Malcolm] Quinn?

1:35:16.708 --> 1:35:17.541
Jeremy?

1:35:18.958 --> 1:35:19.791
My boy!

1:35:20.416 --> 1:35:21.625
[sobbing] My boy!

1:35:22.916 --> 1:35:23.833
[Quinn] Take him.

1:35:25.625 --> 1:35:26.833
Why?

1:35:27.416 --> 1:35:29.916
Tragedy befalls us both, my friend.

1:35:30.416 --> 1:35:32.208
Your boy took my Ffion.

1:35:32.291 --> 1:35:33.666
No, not my boy!

1:35:33.750 --> 1:35:36.166
-What have you done?
-I have brought justice.

1:35:36.250 --> 1:35:37.708
Give me my boy!

1:35:38.458 --> 1:35:39.291
No.

1:35:40.041 --> 1:35:41.791
No, you have no right.

1:35:42.916 --> 1:35:45.666
-I am still the leader of this land!
-Not anymore!

1:35:46.958 --> 1:35:48.833
This man be a false prophet!

1:35:49.875 --> 1:35:51.000
He is weak.

1:35:51.875 --> 1:35:53.041
We've suffered for it.

1:35:53.125 --> 1:35:55.125
I have faltered, aye.

1:35:56.750 --> 1:35:57.875
And I am repentant.

1:35:58.458 --> 1:36:00.041
We can rebuild anew.

1:36:00.166 --> 1:36:01.416
Ask yourselves...

1:36:02.208 --> 1:36:04.500
who will see us through
these dark days?

1:36:04.583 --> 1:36:08.125
Who will see to it
that this land sustains us?

1:36:08.583 --> 1:36:11.666
Who... will drive a spear

1:36:11.750 --> 1:36:16.125
through the hearts
of those that oppose our god?

1:36:16.458 --> 1:36:18.750
-But at what cost?
-Whatever it takes.

1:36:22.250 --> 1:36:23.625
Prove yourself.

1:36:25.666 --> 1:36:29.000
This man... is the enemy
we have long sought.

1:36:29.583 --> 1:36:31.291
He seeks to destroy...

1:36:32.291 --> 1:36:33.666
our way of life.

1:36:36.375 --> 1:36:37.541
We demand justice!

1:36:39.083 --> 1:36:39.958
Do we not?

1:36:45.458 --> 1:36:47.250
Before the eyes of your child...

1:36:47.958 --> 1:36:49.625
and all that doubt you...

1:36:51.083 --> 1:36:52.458
take this man's life.

1:37:07.666 --> 1:37:08.666
Father, don't.

1:37:09.500 --> 1:37:10.458
Hush, child.

1:37:15.833 --> 1:37:16.708
Lift him.

1:37:25.625 --> 1:37:27.708
Father, do not mistake this man
as thy enemy.

1:37:27.791 --> 1:37:29.791
Trust me, child, I do not mistake him.

1:37:31.458 --> 1:37:34.583
-I know who this man really is.
-As do I of you!

1:37:36.458 --> 1:37:38.791
Please be not who I fear you have become.

1:37:51.958 --> 1:37:54.541
-[loud gunshot]
-[villagers screaming]

1:37:57.291 --> 1:37:58.833
What are you doing, Frank?

1:37:58.916 --> 1:38:00.916
Stay back! This has to end.

1:38:01.875 --> 1:38:04.458
-Frank? Wait!
-She has to die.

1:38:05.250 --> 1:38:06.500
[Andrea] Father!

1:38:18.708 --> 1:38:21.666
Thomas, stop it. Please! Please...

1:38:35.250 --> 1:38:36.291
[Quinn] This way!

1:39:36.375 --> 1:39:37.583
[gunshot]

1:39:50.291 --> 1:39:51.333
Burn it all down.

1:39:54.541 --> 1:39:55.416
[gunshot]

1:41:09.458 --> 1:41:10.375
Enough!

1:41:11.291 --> 1:41:12.125
Go.

1:41:13.166 --> 1:41:16.916
-Take your hand off my gun, Malcolm.
-It's over, Quinn. Look at him.

1:41:17.000 --> 1:41:18.875
-Let go!
-I said look at him!

1:41:30.416 --> 1:41:31.500
Quinn..

1:41:34.375 --> 1:41:35.875
[creature groaning]

1:41:43.500 --> 1:41:44.333
Agh!

1:41:46.000 --> 1:41:46.833
[thud]

1:43:21.500 --> 1:43:24.375
[goddess moaning and gulping]

1:43:43.083 --> 1:43:44.500
-Jen.
-[whimpering]

1:43:44.583 --> 1:43:45.958
Ssh. It's Thomas.

1:43:46.041 --> 1:43:48.166
It's Tom, it's Tom. Ssh.

1:43:48.250 --> 1:43:50.458
-[whimpering]
-Ssh. It's Tom.

1:43:51.916 --> 1:43:54.083
I'm going to get you out,
I'll get you out.

1:43:54.166 --> 1:43:55.333
I'll get you out.

1:44:00.416 --> 1:44:01.583
Ssh. I've got you.

1:44:02.166 --> 1:44:03.500
Ssh, ssh.

1:44:11.791 --> 1:44:13.541
[whimpering]

1:44:14.708 --> 1:44:16.416
Jennifer! Jennifer! Jennifer!

1:44:16.500 --> 1:44:17.958
-Thomas!
-Ssh, ssh.

1:44:18.750 --> 1:44:20.625
-Ssh, ssh.
-[Jennifer sobbing]

1:44:20.708 --> 1:44:22.708
Let me see you. Let me see you.

1:44:22.791 --> 1:44:24.291
[sobbing]

1:44:24.375 --> 1:44:26.375
-I can't.
-I know. I know. Ssh.

1:44:27.000 --> 1:44:29.000
I am going to get you out of here.

1:44:29.750 --> 1:44:30.791
Ssh.

1:44:30.875 --> 1:44:33.333
Father-- They told me you were dead.

1:44:34.500 --> 1:44:35.625
Well, to him, I was.

1:44:35.708 --> 1:44:36.875
But I'm here now...

1:44:37.916 --> 1:44:38.916
for you.

1:44:39.625 --> 1:44:40.875
[gasps]

1:44:41.375 --> 1:44:43.833
-[roaring]
-[Jennifer screams]

1:44:44.458 --> 1:44:46.208
[sudden silence]

1:45:45.958 --> 1:45:49.125
[Andrea] Upon bended knee,
I call upon Thee.

1:45:50.333 --> 1:45:51.791
Please, Lord...

1:45:53.375 --> 1:45:55.500
protect me in my hour of need.

1:45:58.208 --> 1:45:59.875
And watch over my father.

1:46:04.875 --> 1:46:06.791
Guide me as I seek solace...

1:46:07.458 --> 1:46:10.125
from the hurt of those
who wish to inflict it.

1:46:11.375 --> 1:46:12.750
I beg of You...

1:46:13.333 --> 1:46:14.750
hear my prayer.

1:46:21.541 --> 1:46:23.541
[wood creaking]

1:46:27.000 --> 1:46:29.125
[chains clanking]

1:46:29.208 --> 1:46:31.625
Aaaagghh!

1:46:31.708 --> 1:46:33.208
Aagh!

1:46:33.291 --> 1:46:35.000
Aagh...

1:46:35.750 --> 1:46:37.250
Aaagghh...

1:46:38.458 --> 1:46:40.625
[Thomas grunting]

1:46:47.875 --> 1:46:49.875
[machinery clanking]

1:46:58.791 --> 1:47:00.250
Aaaggh!

1:47:02.000 --> 1:47:02.833
Agh!

1:47:02.916 --> 1:47:04.916
Aaaagghh!

1:47:05.500 --> 1:47:07.333
Agghh...

1:47:08.166 --> 1:47:10.083
Aagghh!

1:47:12.750 --> 1:47:14.500
Aaagghh!

1:47:15.500 --> 1:47:16.416
Agh!

1:47:17.791 --> 1:47:20.000
Aaagghh...

1:47:20.666 --> 1:47:21.625
Aagh...

1:47:22.791 --> 1:47:24.875
Aa-aagghh...

1:47:25.875 --> 1:47:27.166
Aagghh...

1:47:27.750 --> 1:47:29.125
Aagh...

1:47:29.208 --> 1:47:30.458
Aaagghhh!

1:47:30.541 --> 1:47:32.625
-[crunching]
-Aa-aagh!

1:47:35.291 --> 1:47:37.291
Aaagghh!

1:47:37.375 --> 1:47:38.583
Aagh!

1:47:49.041 --> 1:47:52.083
-[cables tightening]
-Aaagghh!

1:47:54.166 --> 1:47:55.458
[creature growling]

1:47:57.208 --> 1:47:59.041
[machinery clanking]

1:48:03.000 --> 1:48:04.958
[creature shrieking]

1:48:30.958 --> 1:48:32.875
[creature gasping]

1:48:37.625 --> 1:48:39.291
[machinery clanking]

1:48:57.166 --> 1:48:58.041
Agh!

1:48:58.666 --> 1:48:59.916
Agh!

1:49:03.083 --> 1:49:04.958
[creature roaring]

1:49:11.833 --> 1:49:12.666
Agh!

1:49:28.750 --> 1:49:30.750
[panting and groaning]

1:49:59.833 --> 1:50:05.291
[speaking in a strange tongue]
Oh, how I've waited for you, my son.

1:50:14.916 --> 1:50:16.458
[vines creaking]

1:51:17.333 --> 1:51:18.875
How dare you!

1:51:19.250 --> 1:51:21.208
My father will see to it that you never--

1:51:21.291 --> 1:51:23.000
Your father can't help you no more, child.

1:51:24.083 --> 1:51:25.166
I saw to it.

1:51:27.666 --> 1:51:28.500
No.

1:51:32.208 --> 1:51:33.041
[Quinn] Years...

1:51:34.166 --> 1:51:36.750
I've sat and watched...

1:51:37.791 --> 1:51:41.208
as those ingrates
gave thanks to your father.

1:51:43.375 --> 1:51:44.500
False prophet...

1:51:45.208 --> 1:51:47.166
hiding behind a false god!

1:51:49.541 --> 1:51:51.125
I should have had that praise!

1:51:52.208 --> 1:51:54.208
Should have been me they thanked!

1:51:56.500 --> 1:51:59.875
After all, it was I that imprisoned her.

1:52:01.000 --> 1:52:04.166
I, who discovered
what she could do for us.

1:52:05.375 --> 1:52:07.000
[goddess screaming]

1:52:08.666 --> 1:52:10.291
[squealing]

1:52:10.916 --> 1:52:12.875
[goddess shrieking]

1:52:17.125 --> 1:52:18.291
Hold her legs down!

1:52:51.666 --> 1:52:53.041
[sobbing]

1:52:55.791 --> 1:52:58.625
[in her tongue] Set me free, my child.

1:53:23.375 --> 1:53:24.583
Forgive me.

1:54:05.791 --> 1:54:07.458
[goddess shrieking]

1:54:15.208 --> 1:54:16.916
[Malcolm panting]

1:54:41.250 --> 1:54:43.208
[Quinn] Your father was right about her.

1:54:43.708 --> 1:54:46.916
You put a god between your enemy
and the people,

1:54:47.666 --> 1:54:51.333
put the word of the Almighty
between the crosshairs of their muskets,

1:54:51.416 --> 1:54:52.541
you'll see!

1:54:53.291 --> 1:54:56.708
The people won't falter... not one bit!

1:54:57.833 --> 1:54:58.666
Faith...

1:54:59.958 --> 1:55:01.291
binds you.

1:55:02.166 --> 1:55:03.125
God...

1:55:03.791 --> 1:55:05.000
slave...

1:55:06.375 --> 1:55:07.250
mine!

1:55:10.041 --> 1:55:10.916
But she's no god.

1:55:13.333 --> 1:55:14.458
She's just a machine.

1:55:15.875 --> 1:55:16.916
You feed her...

1:55:17.458 --> 1:55:18.291
and she...

1:55:19.916 --> 1:55:20.750
delivers.

1:55:29.416 --> 1:55:30.416
Malcolm...

1:55:32.166 --> 1:55:33.250
he was soft.

1:55:36.583 --> 1:55:39.041
When the blood of the animals
stopped working...

1:55:41.166 --> 1:55:42.541
he tried to feed her himself.

1:55:43.833 --> 1:55:44.666
Hm?

1:55:46.416 --> 1:55:48.333
He fell victim... to faith.

1:55:51.750 --> 1:55:53.375
He would have let us all starve.

1:55:55.166 --> 1:55:57.166
Instead of doing what needed to be done.

1:55:57.666 --> 1:56:00.541
Instead of feeding her
what she needed to be fed.

1:56:13.416 --> 1:56:14.291
Look above you.

1:56:16.833 --> 1:56:18.083
That will be your sun...

1:56:19.291 --> 1:56:20.375
your cloud...

1:56:21.291 --> 1:56:22.333
your moon...

1:56:23.791 --> 1:56:26.125
your only way of knowing
that a day has passed.

1:56:27.875 --> 1:56:28.791
And many will.

1:56:33.125 --> 1:56:34.708
For I will save this village.

1:56:37.416 --> 1:56:38.291
You...

1:56:41.125 --> 1:56:42.625
will avail your bodies to me.

1:56:45.291 --> 1:56:46.583
And when it is ripened...

1:56:47.833 --> 1:56:49.083
I will feed her...

1:56:49.916 --> 1:56:52.333
the flesh of your womb.

1:56:53.375 --> 1:56:54.375
And every year...

1:56:56.166 --> 1:56:57.250
we shall celebrate.

1:56:57.333 --> 1:56:58.458
[man] Fire!

1:56:59.375 --> 1:57:00.750
Fire!

1:57:01.541 --> 1:57:02.791
[shouting]

1:57:06.458 --> 1:57:08.583
[screaming and shouting]

1:57:13.000 --> 1:57:14.166
[man] Brothers!

1:57:14.250 --> 1:57:15.083
Sisters!

1:57:15.625 --> 1:57:16.833
Your Bibles!

1:57:16.916 --> 1:57:18.208
Your texts!

1:57:18.291 --> 1:57:19.666
We must leave this island now!

1:57:19.750 --> 1:57:22.125
Quinn! Where's Quinn?

1:57:22.208 --> 1:57:24.166
He took her! He took Andrea!

1:57:24.250 --> 1:57:25.958
-Where?
-The church!

1:57:26.041 --> 1:57:29.791
-Don't let the boat leave without her.
-May God be with you, Mr. Richardson.

1:57:30.375 --> 1:57:31.541
And also with you.

1:57:36.041 --> 1:57:37.250
Unchain us!

1:57:47.416 --> 1:57:48.958
Consider it a mercy.

1:57:54.458 --> 1:57:55.291
Agh!

1:58:09.166 --> 1:58:11.208
-[crunch]
-Aaagh!

1:58:11.625 --> 1:58:12.458
Agh!

1:58:26.208 --> 1:58:27.083
No! No!

1:59:15.250 --> 1:59:17.541
Aaagghhh....

1:59:19.000 --> 1:59:20.791
Aaaghh...!

1:59:25.083 --> 1:59:26.750
[sobbing]

1:59:32.000 --> 1:59:33.083
[panting]

1:59:41.875 --> 1:59:43.500
The boat's waiting for you.

1:59:45.000 --> 1:59:46.375
For all of us.

2:00:12.750 --> 2:00:14.041
We have to go.

2:00:42.625 --> 2:00:43.875
No! Thomas!

2:00:43.958 --> 2:00:46.500
-Go! Leave me...
-No!

2:00:46.583 --> 2:00:49.500
-You'll never make it.
-No! I can't leave you.

2:00:49.583 --> 2:00:51.708
You have to. Look at me, Jen.

2:00:51.791 --> 2:00:54.000
-Please...
-I can't feel my legs.

2:00:54.125 --> 2:00:55.750
[Jennifer] I don't want to lose you again.

2:00:55.833 --> 2:00:57.958
[Thomas] You never did,
and you never will.

2:00:59.541 --> 2:01:01.083
Don't do this...

2:01:01.583 --> 2:01:02.500
Not now!

2:01:02.916 --> 2:01:06.750
This world... has taken so much from me.

2:01:07.708 --> 2:01:11.583
But in all my pain,
even in my darkest days,

2:01:11.666 --> 2:01:15.416
I swore...
I swore it would never take you.

2:01:18.458 --> 2:01:21.375
Now go, get on that boat,

2:01:21.458 --> 2:01:25.375
live, and be the light
that guides me to eternity.

2:01:31.791 --> 2:01:33.250
Always in my heart.

2:01:37.458 --> 2:01:39.916
And you... And you in mine.

2:01:43.708 --> 2:01:44.750
